We're writing a proxy which uses Jsoup. Connection.execute throws up HTTP 304 errors on every other request.

I can't figure out how to get Jsoup to tell apache to not send me 304s and just give me the data.

java.io.IOException: 304 error loading URL http://localhost/asdf

I tried doing this before the request, didn't fix it. I'm not sure if I need to set some setting in Jsoup or in the headers sent over. I've also tried disabling cache on apache, but couldn't figure that out either. :(

        con.header("Last-Modified", "Wed, 15 Nov 1995 04:58:08 GMT" );
        con.header("Cache-control", "no-cache");
        con.header("Cache-store", "no-store");
        con.header("Pragma", "no-cache");
        con.header("Expires", "0");

